Program: Outlook
Title: 09/02/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00ndjgp
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 13 Feb 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, Najia Essayed tells us how her life was affected by Libya's first revolution, and how she's trying to influence the outcome for women of the second. Also, a rare insight into the life of Sri Lanka's indigenous Vedda community. And Zane Ibrahim shares his experiences of the pioneering days of community radio in South Africa. Show less